      • validateLangStr

        public static void validateLangStr(String languageCodeStr)
        Method to validate comma delimited language code string. This method will throw exception:-
        a) If the number of language codes specified is greater than the maximum allowed
        b) For invalid/unsupported language codes.
        Parameters:
        languageCodeStr - comma delimited string of language codes
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - This method will throw IllegalArgumentException for language string containing unsupported languages or more than the number of languages allowed
